Diamond Bank of Nigeria Falls to One-Week Low on Loss Forecast

-- B y   V i n c e n t   N w a n m a
-- 
2011-09-08T14:22:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-08/diamond-bank-of-nigeria-falls-to-one-week-low-on-loss-forecast.html
Diamond Bank Plc (DIAMONDB) , a Nigerian lender
with operations in four other African nations, fell the most in
more than a week after it forecast a loss for the fourth
quarter.  The stock retreated 1.2 percent, its biggest decline since
Aug. 29, to 4.15 naira, the lowest since Sept. 1, by the 2:30
p.m. close in Lagos.  Diamond expects to report a loss of about 454.4 million
naira ($3 million) for the fourth quarter, it said in a
statement published on the website of the  Nigerian Stock
Exchange  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Nwanma in Lagos at 
 vnwanma@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
